From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 06:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: dsa: add rtl8372n driver scaffolding

Adds a new standalone driver for the Realtek RTL8372N / RTL8373 family
of managed switches that hang off the host SoC's MDIO bus, used in
IPQ5332-based routers (GL.iNet Flint 3 GL-BE9300 and likely others).

This patch only adds the Kconfig + Makefile entries. The .c file itself
lives at target/linux/qualcommbe/files-6.12/drivers/net/dsa/rtl8372n.c
in this work tree so we can iterate on it without re-generating a
patch every edit.

First-cut driver covers probe + chip-ID detection only — enough to
prove the DT binding and the MDIO indirect protocol. Port + VLAN
support is follow-up work.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/dsa/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/Kconfig
@@ -161,4 +161,18 @@
 	  This enables support for the Vitesse VSC7385, VSC7388, VSC7395
 	  and VSC7398 SparX integrated ethernet switches, connected over
 	  a CPU-attached address bus and work in memory-mapped I/O mode.
+config NET_DSA_RTL8372N
+	tristate "Realtek RTL8372N / RTL8373 family switch support"
+	depends on NET_DSA && OF
+	select NET_DSA_TAG_RTL8_4
+	help
+	  Enable support for the Realtek RTL8372N and RTL8373 family of
+	  managed switches. Used in IPQ5332-based routers (e.g. GL.iNet
+	  Flint 3 GL-BE9300) where the LAN ports sit behind a Realtek
+	  switch chip attached on the SoC's MDIO bus.
+
+	  The first-cut driver provides probe + chip-ID detection only;
+	  port and VLAN support is still under development.
+
+
 endmenu
--- a/drivers/net/dsa/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/Makefile
@@ -18,6 +18,7 @@
 obj-$(CONFIG_NET_DSA_VITESSE_VSC73XX) += vitesse-vsc73xx-core.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_NET_DSA_VITESSE_VSC73XX_PLATFORM) += vitesse-vsc73xx-platform.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_NET_DSA_VITESSE_VSC73XX_SPI) += vitesse-vsc73xx-spi.o
+obj-$(CONFIG_NET_DSA_RTL8372N)	+= rtl8372n.o
 obj-y				+= b53/
 obj-y				+= hirschmann/
 obj-y				+= microchip/
